A 32-YEAR-OLD driver, Mayowa Adeyemo has been remanded in Ilesha Correctional Centre for allegedly battering his 18-month-old son with burning cigarettes. Adeyemo was arraigned before an Osun State Magistrates’ Court Osogbo on Tuesday on two counts bothering on assault and exploitation. Police prosecutor Abiodun Fagboyinbo told the court that the defendant beat the child with a stick and burned him with a cigarette. Adeyemo, who did not have legal representation, said, “I have five children from five different mothers. Several pastors I consulted told me that my mother was the one bewitching me. I am a taxi driver but things have not been fine for me. The son I assaulted with sticks is the son that my fourth wife bore for me.” Chief Magistrate Modupe Awodele remanded Adeyemo in Ilesha Correctional Centre and adjourned the case to July 14. The Nation OSOGBO - A commercial driver, Mayowa Adeyemo, 32, on Tuesday, appeared before an Osun State Magistrates’ Court sitting in Osogbo for battering his 18-month-old son. Mayowa was alleged to have beaten the victim with sticks and burnt several parts of his body with lighted cigarettes. The police prosecutor, Abiodun Fagboyinbo,… June 17, 2020 In "Metro" By Moji Eniola Ikeja - A principal of a secondary school in Lagos, Samson Adeyemo, has admitted before an Ikeja Special Offences Court that he had sexual relationships with two 17-year-old twin students of his school. Adeyemo, 41, who resides at No. 8, Odesanya St., Abule Egba, near Lagos, is… January 13, 2020 In "Metro" •Bose Abiodun Thirty-five-year old Bose Abiodun, who has four children, spent 25 months in Ilesha Correctional Centre after her husband, Femi – under trial for manslaughter – whom she stood surety for, jumped bail. Abiodun, who had her fourth child in prison, shares her experience with BOLA BAMIGBOLA What do… June 6, 2020 In "Interview"